    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In geomorphology, islands formed through fluvial processes, such as the erosion and deposition of sediment by a stream or river; they are surrounded by flowing water or stream branches or waterways and have established permanent vegetation. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
